AbstractAgentTab, AbstractDeviceTab, AdverseEventTab, AeTab, AssignParticipantTab, AssignStudyTab, BasicsTab, CreateParticipantReviewParticipantTab, CreateParticipantTab, EditParticipantReviewParticipantTab, EditParticipantTab, NotificationsTab, OrganizationTab, ReportDeliveryDefinitionTab, ReportMandatoryFieldDefinitionTab, ReviewAssignmentTab, ReviewTab, SelectRuleTypeTab, SelectStudyForParticipantTab, StudyTab, SubjectMedHistoryTab, SubmitReportResultTab, SubmitReportTab, SubmitterTab, UserTab
public abstract class TabWithFields<C>
extends InPlaceEditableTab<C>

The central class in the fields package. Subclasses may provide a map of InputFieldGroups. This map will be provided to the view (in the request attribute fieldGroups). It will also be used to to basic (required/not required) field validation.

Author:
Rhett Sutphin, Ion C. Olaru, Biju Joseph
See Also:
InputField, InputFieldGroup

populateHelpAttributeOnFields

protected void populateHelpAttributeOnFields(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,InputFieldGroup> groupMap)
This functions sets the HELP key in the attribute map associated to an InputField. The default logic of deriving HELP key is "viewName" + "." + propertyName, where / character in viewName is replaced with . (dot) and array notations[x] in propertyName removed .
